# <%= current_page.data.title %>

**Note: This is currently only available to Civil Servants**

To gain access to GitHub Copilot you will need to create a pull request against the [opg-org-infra repository](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/opg-org-infra) adding you to the `opg-copilot-users` team with the following commit message.

```text
Allocate <your name> a GitHub Copilot licence

In requesting a GitHub Copilot licence, I acknowledge my responsibility to personally understand the full functionality of any AI-assisted code I submit for peer review, and that it meets the same high standards and conventions of Justice Digital and OPG Digital.
```

## Step by step instructions

This assumes you are already familiar with git, have created an appropriate branch, and are present in the users.tf.
If you are not already in the users.tf then consult the relevant guide for being added to the organisation.

1. Find yourself in the [users.tf](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/opg-org-infra/blob/main/access-management/users.tf)
1. Add `module.gh_team_copilot_users.id` to your github_teams array
